2116JSC::IsoSubspace* JSPaintRenderingContext2D::subspaceForImpl(JSC::VM& vm)
2117{
2118 auto& clientData = *static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
2119 auto& spaces = clientData.subspaces();
2120 if (auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForPaintRenderingContext2D.get())
2121 return space;
2122 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSPaintRenderingContext2D> || !JSPaintRenderingContext2D::needsDestruction);
2123 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSPaintRenderingContext2D>)
2124 spaces.m_subspaceForPaintRenderingContext2D = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.destructibleObjectHeapCellType.get(), JSPaintRenderingContext2D);
2125 else
2126 spaces.m_subspaceForPaintRenderingContext2D = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.cellHeapCellType.get(), JSPaintRenderingContext2D);
2127 auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForPaintRenderingContext2D.get();
2128IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("unreachable-code")
2129IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("tautological-compare")
2130 void (*myVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSPaintRenderingContext2D::visitOutputConstraints;
2131 void (*jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSC::JSCell::visitOutputConstraints;
2132 if (myVisitOutputConstraint != jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)
2133 clientData.outputConstraintSpaces().append(space);
2134IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
2135IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
2136 return space;

2203 // to toJS() we currently require PaintRenderingContext2D you to opt out of binding hardening
2204 // by adding the SkipVTableValidation attribute to the interface IDL definition
